  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Technical Assistance Support to Scale up Routine Immunization Services to Internally Displaced People (IDPs), Returnees, and Conflict-Affected Host Communities Residing in Hard-To-Reach Areas in Wau, Rubkona, and Malakal Counties of South Sudan</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project contributes to increased immunization coverage of children 0 to 23 months by scaling up routine immunization services to internally displaced people (IDPs), returnees, and conflict-affected host communities residing in hard-to-reach areas in Wau, Rubkona, and Malakal counties. Conflict, insecurity, and natural disasters have displaced nearly four million people since 2013, of whom 1.6 million are IDPs.  The IDPs reside in congested camps and camp-like settings, mainly in rural areas. South Sudan is also home to more than 300,000 refugees and a growing number of migrants, mainly from the region.</narrative>
  </description>
